            , his master.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-380-person2715">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SMELLIE
               <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2715" type="surname" value="SMELLIE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2715" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2715" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am brother-in-law of 
               <persName id="t18310908-380-person2716">
                  James 
                  Squire
               <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2716" type="surname" value="Squire"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2716" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2716" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , a <rs id="t18310908-380-viclabel1952" type="occupation">pork-butcher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-380-victim2714 t18310908-380-viclabel1952"></join>, of Tottenham-court-road. My sister gave me information; the prisoner had been in their service about twelve weeks, and on the 1st of September I called him into the parlour, and told him his master was very dissatisfied with his conduct; and asked him to account for some meat which we had found concealed - I did not threaten or promise him at all; I asked him what money he had about him; he said 16s. 6d. - I asked him to show it me, which he did; there were two half-crowns among it - I sent for Cowley; when he came I showed him the whole money - he picked out a half-crown and a shilling, in the prisoner's presence, and said they had been in his possession that morning - I then gave the prisoner in charge; the rest of the money was identified at the office.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-380-person2717">
                  WILLIAM 
                  COWLEY
               <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2717" type="surname" value="COWLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2717" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2717" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 31st of August, Mrs. Squire sent to me, and gave me two half-crowns and one shilling and sixpence; I marked them all, and sent my sister next morning with a half-crown and a shilling to purchase some meat, about a quarter before eight o'clock, and about eight, I sent her daughter with the other halfcrown and sixpence - I was sent for at eleven that morn<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183109080156"></xptr>ing; Smellie produced a quantity of money from the prisoner's pocket, among which I identified the half-crown and a shilling which I had marked - Squire has four or five servants - I said the money was marked; the prisoner said he had not seen me that morning, which was true.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-380-person2718">
                  MARY 
                  YOUSTON
               <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2718" type="surname" value="YOUSTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2718" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2718" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am Cowley's sister. On the morning of the 1st of September I went to Squires' shop, and bought some pork, for which I paid the prisoner the halfcrown and shilling; I received it of my brother - I saw the same money before the Magistrate, marked in the same way.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-380-person2719">
                  JOHN 
                  FINLEY
               <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2719" type="surname" value="FINLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2719" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2719" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Policeman. On the 1st of September, about one o'clock, the prisoner was given into my charge for stealing money out of a till - I produce the half-crown and shilling.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-380-person2720">
                  WILLIAM 
                  COWLEY
               <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2720" type="surname" value="COWLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2720" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2720" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . This half-crown and shilling I marked, at seven o'clock on the evening of the 31st; here is the same mark on another half-crown.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was in the habit of serving in the shop early in the morning; a girl came and I served her; there was no key to lock the till, and I put the money into my pocket, while I went to the back premises for some liver, and forgot to take it out again.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-380-person2721">
                  MARY 
                  YOUSTON
               <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2721" type="surname" value="YOUSTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2721" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-380-person2721" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am quite sure he put the money into the till.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310908-380-verdict1953" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310908-380-verdict1953" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-380-verdict1953" type="verdictSubcategory" value="withRecommendation"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 19.</p>
               <p>Recommended to Mercy. - <rs id="t18310908-380-punish1954" type="punishmentDescription">
